p.font: The use case diagram presents the performance of the role of the main actors like the customer, seller and manager responsible for the system, whose interactions sum up the process of buying one or more generic items and services in a garden centre.

To the extent that the product or service is purchased by the customer, the system begins through the checkout objects, which in turn relates to the activities like financial transactions and updates of labour and items available.
Once the previously mentioned stage is completed, through reports it is possible to manage the need to reposition the items sold and allocate available labour.
